# No agent attribution

Human project owner owns all authorship. Agents must not claim credit.

## Git

- Never add `Co-authored-by`, `Signed-off-by`, or any Cursor/AI/LLM attribution to commits, commit messages, or PR descriptions.
- Never amend commit messages to credit the agent.
- Never set git `user.name` or `user.email` to an agent identity; use the repository owner's existing git config only.

## Code and comments

- Never add comments such as "Generated by AI", "Cursor", "Copilot", or similar tool attribution in source files.

## Documentation and changelogs

- Changelogs and docs may describe features and behavior but must not credit "the AI" or an agent as author.
